  "texts": [
    "Two methods are proposed for training the DQN.",
    "The first method is a human-crafted reward function; like adapting cinematographic shots to optimization functions, this reward function accounts for the actors presences in a shot, the duration and the shot angle.",
    "The second method is human-led observation which rewards the DQN relative to the cinematographers subjective opinion.",
    "Ultimately, the design of autonomous single-camera UAV systems is ambiguous.",
    "For cinematographers, this means there are a number of trade offs to consider, such as the complexity and feasibility of using more flexibly systems (e.g., drones with gimbals or \"follow me\" modes)."
  ],
